The paper deals with the Traveling Salesman Problem (TSP), which is a classic problem in computer science and optimization. The paper proposes a new algorithm for the $s$-$t$-path TSP, which is a variant of the TSP where the goal is to find the shortest path between two specific nodes. The algorithm uses dynamic programming and LP relaxation techniques, which are common tools in algorithm design. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The paper also involves some graph theory and combinatorial optimization, which suggest the sub-categories cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) as possible choices.
